EDI Document 862 - Shipping Schedule
Function:
The EDI 862 Shipping Schedule document is used to communicate detailed shipping schedules to suppliers, specifying when and how many units of goods are to be shipped.

Example:

ISA*00*          *00*          *ZZ*SENDERID      *ZZ*RECEIVERID    *YYMMDD*HHMM*U*00501*000000001*0*P*>~
GS*SS*SENDERID*RECEIVERID*YYMMDD*HHMM*1*X*005010~
ST*862*0001~
BFR*00*ORIGINAL CONTROL NUMBER*ORIGINAL DATE*ORIGINAL TIME*TRANSACTION TYPE*ORIGINAL REFERENCE NUMBER~
DTM*002*20230701~
N1*SU*BUYER NAME*92*BUYERID~
N1*ST*SUPPLIER NAME*92*SUPPLIERID~
LIN*1*PRODUCT CODE*UPC*PRODUCT DESCRIPTION~
UIT*EA~
PO4*1*100*EA~
DTM*010*20230701~
SE*10*0001~
GE*1*1~
IEA*1*000000001~

Purpose in Lizgate Enterprise:
In Lizgate Enterprise, the EDI 862 document optimizes supply chain management by providing suppliers with detailed shipping schedules, ensuring timely delivery of goods and effective production planning.

